│ The bug is in the `SLPVectorizer`'s logic for cleaning up scalar instructions after        │
│ vectorization, specifically within the `removeInstructionsAndOperands` function. When      │
│ vectorizing a horizontal reduction, an instruction that is part of the reduction tree      │
│ might also be an operand for another instruction that is scheduled for vectorization in a  │
│ different tree. The vectorizer prematurely tries to delete this shared instruction,        │
│ causing an assertion failure because the instruction still has a user in the other         │
│ (not-yet-vectorized) tree.                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to make the cleanup logic in `removeInstructionsAndOperands` more robust.       │
│ Before attempting to delete an instruction, we must check if it has any users that are     │
│ themselves scheduled for vectorization (i.e., they are part of a `TreeEntry`). If such a   │
│ user exists and has not been deleted yet, we should skip the deletion of the current       │
│ instruction. This ensures that shared instructions are only removed after all their        │
│ vectorized users have been processed.                                                      │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will modify `BoUpSLP::removeInstructionsAndOperands` to add this check. The function is  │
│ a template, and the change needs to be applied within the loop that erases the             │
│ instructions.                                                                              │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                      │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                      │
│ @@ -2745,6 +2745,15 @@                                                                     │
│      auto *I = cast<Instruction>(V);                                                       │
│      if (!I->getParent())                                                                  │
│        continue;                                                                           │
│ +    // If the instruction has a user that is going to be vectorized, do not               │
│ +    // delete it.                                                                         │
│ +    if (any_of(I->users(), [this](User *U) {                                              │
│ +          Instruction *UserI = cast<Instruction>(U);                                      │
│ +          return !isDeleted(UserI) && getTreeEntry(UserI);                                │
│ +        })) {                                                                             │
│ +      I->dropAllReferences();                                                             │
│ +      continue;                                                                           │
│ +    }                                                                                     │
│      assert((I->use_empty() || all_of(I->uses(),                                           │
│                                       [&](Use &U) {                                        │
│                                         return isDeleted(                                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
